{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01G7B8ur5M5NAip1HxoksAJw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of the current state:\n- 3 RabbitMQ nodes running 3.12.14 on Erlang 25.3.2.15\n- `/app` vhost exists with `app-queue` (5 messages, durable) and `app-backup` (20 messages, durable)\n- Using k8s peer discovery\n- `queue_master_locator = min-masters` is deprecated in newer versions\n\n**Upgrade path from 3.12 to 4.1:**\n\nRabbitMQ does not support skipping major versions, but 3.12 to 4.1 should be a supported upgrade path as 3.13 was an intermediate version, but actually:\n- 4.0 requires 3.13 as the minimum source, so I can't jump directly from 3.12 to 4.0\n- The proper sequence would be 3.12 → 3.13 → 4.0 → 4.1\n\nFor the rolling upgrade in Kubernetes, I need to account for feature flags and data compatibility—the StatefulSet will update pods one by one starting from the highest ordinal, meaning old and new versions will run simultaneously during the transition, which requires careful handling of version compatibility.\n\nLooking at what's actually available, `rabbitmq:4.1-management` exists on Docker Hub, but the safest path from 3.12 is likely 3.12 → 3.13 → 4.1 since direct jumps may require intermediate steps for feature flag compatibility. Looking at the feature flags that need to be enabled in 4.1, I see a significant list including quorum_queue and stream_queue support, plus several others. I also need to account for breaking changes: classic mirrored queues are completely removed in 4.x, so the `ha-mode` policy won't work anymore, and the `queue_master_locator = min-masters` configuration needs to be removed before upgrading.\n\nFor the upgrade from 3.12 to 4.1, my approach is to first verify the queue types in the current setup to ensure there are no classic mirrored queues that would be incompatible with 4.x.\n\nThen I need to update the ConfigMap to remove the deprecated `queue_master_locator` setting, which has been renamed to `queue_leader_locator` in newer versions and will cause compatibility issues. After that, I can proceed with a rolling upgrade by updating the StatefulSet image directly to 4.1 and monitoring the process.\n\nI'm also considering whether a direct jump from 3.12 to 4.1 is viable—the official recommendation is to upgrade from 3.13, but in this test environment I can attempt the direct path and fall back to a two-step upgrade if needed. The rolling upgrade process works by stopping one node at a time, starting it with the new version, and letting it rejoin the cluster with only the feature flags supported by all nodes until the upgrade completes. Since 3.12 to 4.0 is a supported upgrade path, I can proceed with updating the ConfigMap to remove the deprecated `queue_master_locator` setting and then rolling out the new image to the StatefulSet, monitoring as each pod updates sequentially.\n\nI need to check the RabbitMQ 4.x configuration changes—the `queue_master_locator` setting was renamed to `queue_leader_locator` in 3.13 and may be ignored or trigger warnings in 4.x. Also, the `classic_mirrored_queue_version` feature flag being enabled doesn't necessarily mean we have actual mirrored queues, just that the capability was available, so I should verify the actual queue configuration before proceeding.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1352,"cache_read_input_tokens":34295,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1352},"output_tokens":22,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8eeafaa6-fedc-4c75-a366-87afff4c3d00","uuid":"e436c654-9785-4ff3-93e9-66488d646e0e","request_id":"req_011CcdEMytieCew91ADyS3MN"}
