{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WGAgpmvqGpGu8S3tHPsD1s","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `khepri_db` feature flag is still disabled. This is fine for 3.13 - Khepri is optional in 3.13 but may become required in 4.x. Let me check if I should enable it.\n\nActually, in RabbitMQ 4.0+:\n- Khepri becomes the required metadata store\n- The migration from Mnesia to Khepri is done by enabling the `khepri_db` feature flag\n- In 4.0, this may be automatically enabled\n\nFor the upgrade path:\n- In 3.13, Khepri is optional while Mnesia remains the default\n- In 4.0 and later, Khepri is the default and required\n- The question is whether to enable `khepri_db` now on 3.13 before upgrading to 4.1, or let it happen automatically during the upgrade itself\n- According to the RabbitMQ documentation, the Khepri migration happens automatically when you enable the `khepri_db` feature flag, and in RabbitMQ 4.0, this flag is enabled by default\n- If you upgrade a node to 4.0 while other nodes are still on 3.13, the mixed cluster might work but you should complete the upgrade and then enable all feature flags\n- The safest approach seems to be not enabling `khepri_db` on 3.13 since it's optional and could cause issues if other nodes haven't been migrated yet, letting the 4.1 upgrade handle the Khepri migration instead\n- In practice, 4.0 nodes can start up and migrate from Mnesia to Khepri automatically when the `khepri_db` feature flag is enabled, which 4.0 does by default\n- According to the RabbitMQ 4.0 release notes, Khepri becomes the default metadata store and the migration happens automatically once the last node in the cluster is upgraded to 4.0 or later\n- During a rolling upgrade with mixed versions, the cluster continues using Mnesia until all nodes are upgraded, then Khepri activates automatically\n- So I should just proceed with upgrading to 4.1 and let the Khepri migration happen on its own without manual intervention","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":249,"cache_read_input_tokens":45113,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":249},"output_tokens":30,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8eeafaa6-fedc-4c75-a366-87afff4c3d00","uuid":"34a693b4-99dd-4f3d-a337-ccfc2775c063","request_id":"req_011CcdEewSrK8R4Wz6FVutnF"}
